<TITLE> Govt, AL, BNP condemn attack on Bhutto rally </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 19 (bdnews24.com)  The government Friday condemned the bomb attack on the motorcade of the former Pakistan prime minister Benazir Bhutto in Karachi. The Awami League and the BNP also expressed concern at suspected suicide blasts on her convoy that left more than 133 dead and hundreds injured. Foreign ministry spokesman Nazmul Kaunain in a signed statement said, "The attack is cowardly." He expressed sympathy to the members of those killed and injured in the incident. Acting AL president Zillur Rahman and acting general secretary Syed Ashraful Islam in a joint statement condemned the suicide attack on Bhutto's public rally. They said the attack was barbarous and the perpetrators were enemy of the humanity. The leaders urged the world community to take action against the attackers. Pro-reform BNP leader Abdul Mannan Bhuiyan in a statement said, "The militant attack is barbarous and cowardly. The humanity will have to act against these attackers in unison. "The attackers are enemy of peace and humanity." BNP secretary general Khandaker Delwar Hossain in a statement termed the attack cowardly. "This attack is in no way acceptable. All have to be united to resist these enemies of humanity." Both Bhuiyan and Delwar sympathised with the families of those killed and injured. bdnew
